---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-4 py-16 sm:py-24 lg:py-32">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-[12px] leading-4 text-mute font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.5px] mb-3">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-[32px] font-semibold leading-[40px] tracking-[-1.28px] text-ink sm:text-[48px] sm:leading-[48px] sm:tracking-[-2.4px]">
        Privacy Policy.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[16px] leading-6 text-body">
        Last updated: July 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-[16px] leading-6 text-body">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Our Privacy Promise</h2>
        <p>
          base64go.com is a privacy-first tool. <strong class="text-ink font-medium">We do not collect, store, or transmit any of your data.</strong> All encoding and decoding happens entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. Your input never leaves your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Data Collection</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">We do not collect:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5">
          <li>Text you type or paste into the tool</li>
          <li>Files you upload or drag-and-drop</li>
          <li>Output generated by the tool</li>
          <li>Personal information of any kind</li>
          <li>IP addresses or browsing history</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          There are <strong class="text-ink font-medium">no user accounts, no sign-ups, and no cookies</strong> used for tracking. The only data stored locally in your browser is your theme preference (light/dark mode) and operation history &mdash; both saved using localStorage and never transmitted anywhere.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          We use your browser's localStorage to save two things: your theme preference and your recent encode/decode history (up to 20 entries). This data stays on your device and can be cleared at any time using the "Clear All" button in the History panel or by clearing your browser data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Google Fonts</strong> to load the Inter and JetBrains Mono typefaces. Google may collect usage data when fetching these fonts. We do not use any analytics, advertising, or tracking services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Hosting</h2>
        <p>
          The website is hosted on a static hosting platform. Our hosting provider may collect standard server logs (such as request URLs and timestamps) for operational purposes. These logs do not include the content you process with the tool, as all processing happens on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold leading-7 tracking-[-0.6px] text-ink mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@base64go.com" class="text-link hover:text-link-deep">privacy@base64go.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
